Label: PESC College Transcript Terms
Comment: RDF terms defined by PESC for College Transcripts.

Label: Created Date Time
Comment: The date and Time stamp when the document was created.

Label: Destination
Comment: The destination or recipient of the transcript being sent.

Label: Document Complete Code
Comment: Indicates whether the document conveys a complete record

Label: Document ID
Comment: Identifier for this document.
Usage Note: The general practice is that the identifier includes the date and time plus other identifying data.

Label: Document Official Code
Comment: Indicates if the document is unofficial.

Label: Document Process Code
Comment: Indicates a TEST or PRODUCTION document.

Label: Document type Code
Comment: The type and purpose of document being transmitted.

Label: Request Tracking ID
Comment: The Unique ID associated with a request action that is returned to the requestor for document matching and tracking.

Label: Source
Comment: Indicates the source of the Transcript being sent.  It is normally the sending school where the student enrolled for courses.

Label: student
Comment: The person who is the subject of this transcript.

Label: Transmission Type
Comment: The nature of the transmission.

Label: Academic Honors
Comment: Honors information for an academic award.

Label: Academic Summary Level
Comment: The level of credit associated with the credit hours earned for the course.

Label: Academic Summary Type
Comment: Indication of what is being summarized over which period of time.

Label: Class Rank
Comment: The student's class rank relative to other students in their academic cohort (e.g. class).

Label: Class Rank Date
Comment: The date on which the student was included in the class ranking and the class was ranked.

Label: Class Rank Session count
Comment: The number of sessions of coursework included in the ranking of the student in the class.

Label: Class Rank Year
Comment: The year on which the student was included in the class ranking and the class was ranked.

Label: Class Rank Year Month
Comment: The year and month in which the student was included in the class ranking and the class was ranked.

Label: Class Size
Comment: The numeric size of the academic cohort (e.g. class).

Label: Credit Hours Attempted
Comment: The total value of credit hours attempted whether or not included in the hours for GPA or hours earned.

Label: Credit Hours Deficient
Comment: The total value of credit hours the student is lacking in order to successfully complete requirements for an award, diploma or certificate.

Label: Credit Hours Earned
Comment: The total value of credit hours successfully completed or earned.

Label: Credit Hours For GPA
Comment: The total value of credit hours used to calculate the Grade Point Average.

Label: Credit Hours Required
Comment: The total value of credit hours that are required for the award or diploma for which the student is pursuing.

Label: Credit Unit
Comment: The type of credit (unit, semester, or quarter) associated with the credit hours earned for the course.

Label: Delinquencies
Comment: The academic standing of the student upon transfer to the institution.

Label: Entry Date
Comment: The date on which the student officially was admitted to the school or when the student first attended the school.

Label: Exit Date
Comment: The date on which the student officially withdrew, was withdrawn, or graduated.

Label: Exit Reason Code
Comment: The reason the student stopped attending.  It is a code set approved by the US Department of Education's National Center for Education Statistics and is included in the NCES Handbook.

Label: GPA Range Maximum
Comment: The maximum possible GPA.

Label: GPA Range Minimum
Comment: The minimum possible GPA.

Label: Grade Point Average
Comment: The value of the total quality points divided by the Credit Hours for Grade Point Average.

Label: High School Credit Summary
Comment: A summary of credits taken at a secondary school

Label: Honors Level
Comment: A code value representing 1st highest honor, 2nd highest and 3rd highest.

Label: Honors Title
Comment: e descriptive title for the honors received.

Label: Total Quality Points
Comment: The total value of quality points used for the calculation of the Grade Point Average.

Label: Academic Completion Date
Comment: The date on which the student's requirements for the degree or diploma were met or completed.

Label: Academic Completion Indicator
Comment: An indication that the degree-seeking student completed all of the requirements for his or her academic program.  Not used for Non-Degree programs.

Label: Academic Degree Requirement
Comment: Thesis or dissertation information if required for the award.

Label: Conditions Met Code
Comment: Indicates whether and how conditions for the requirement have been attained.

Label: Conditions Met Date
Comment: Date requirement was met.

Label: Course Academic Supplemental Grade Status Code
Comment: Special enrollment or completion status of this course

Label: Course Equivalent Grade
Comment: The alternate grade including the grade and its scale.

Label: Course Grade
Comment: Grade for the course.

Label: Course Supplemental Grade
Comment: Grades that are reported, which combine to make the final grade in a course.

Label: Score Invalidated Indicator
Comment: Indicates if the score has been invalidated.  If true, score previously reported for this test and test date is not valid.

Label: Score Revised Indicator
Comment: Indicates if the score report has been revised.  If true, score may differ from score previously reported for this test and test date

Label: Score Self Reported Indicator
Comment: Indicates if the score has been self-reported by the student.

Label: Score Value
Comment: The actual value of the score received on the test

Label: Student Level
Comment: Used to indicate the classification or grade level of the student at the time the transcript is being sent, or the last classification or grade level of the student.

Label: Supplemental Grade
Comment: Grades that are reported, which combine to make the final grade in a course.

Label: Supplemental Grade Code
Comment: The type of component grade that is being included for an education course.

Label: Supplemental Grade Sub Session
Comment: This is the numeric count of the subsession of a course.
Usage Note: The earliest subsession would have the value of "1".  The next would be "2", etc.  Each would be a positive whole number.

Label: Test Date
Comment: Date of the test.

Label: Test Year
Comment: Date of the test when only the year is available.

Label: Test Year Month
Comment: Date of the test when only the month and year are available.

Label: Thesis Dissertation Advisor
Comment: The advisor (Major Professor) supervising the Thesis or Dissertation on behalf of the student earning the degree.

Label: Thesis Dissertation Title
Comment: The title of the thesis or dissertation.

Label: URL Address
Comment: The Internet web address where a copy of the thesis or dissertation may be obtained

Label: Agency Assigned ID
Comment: The ID assigned by the state or province or an agency, to the person (student).

Label: Birth City
Comment: The city in which the person was born.

Label: Birth Country
Comment: The name of the country in which the person was born.

Label: Birthday
Comment: Month and Day of Birth.

Label: Birth State Province Code
Comment: The state, province, or extra-state jurisdiction in which the person was born.

Label: Birth Year
Comment: Year of Birth.

Label: Cohort Graduation Year
Comment: The school year in which the student entered the baseline group used for computing completion rates, e.g., high school year and program.

Label: Composite Name
Comment: The full name of the person in Last NameSuffix, First Middle order; comma after last name or NameSuffix.

Label: Country
Comment: Name of the country which the claimant states as the country of permanent residence.

Label: Country Code
Comment: Code indicating Country.

Label: County
Comment: Name of the county which the claimant states as the county of permanent residence.

Label: County Code
Comment: A code identifying the county which the applicant claims as the permanent residence.
Usage Note: This is a 5-digit code which includes state (2 digits) and county within a state (3 digits).

Label: Deceased Indicator
Comment: Indicates the person is deceased.

Label: Gender Code
Comment: The gender of the Student

Label: Residency
Comment: A code indicating where the student currently resides.

Label: Language Proficiency
Comment: Adeptness in comprehending and using the language.

Label: Name Code
Comment: The type of name.

Label: Residency Status Code
Comment: Declaration made by the claimant as to his or her permanent residency.

Label: State Province
Comment: The literal name of the state, province or territory of a postal address of the source of this document.
Usage Note: Use for addresses outside US or Canada.

Label: State Province Code
Comment: The state, province, or extra-state jurisdiction in which the person was born.

Label: Accrediation Body Code
Comment: The acronym for the regional or other accrediting body that has given accreditation to the school sending the high school transcript.

Label: School Level
Comment: Indicates level of school.

Label: Attention Line
Comment: The individual or office name within the postal address where inquiries should be directed.

Label: Country Prefix Code
Comment: International dialing code.

Label: Email Address
Comment: Email address of the contact.

Label: FAX Phone
Comment: Fax phone number of the contact.

Label: Phone
Comment: Phone contact details.

Label: Phone Number
Comment: The phone number of the contact without contry prefix code or extension.

Label: Phone Number Extension
Comment: The extended telephone addressing information used in addition to phone number such as a PBX extension, a pager PIN, or FAX sub-address.

Label: URL
Comment: The Uniform Resource Locator of the contact.
